{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4b89d855-936a-4625-bd2f-31548bc8888b","content":"Here are the three breaking changes and their fixes:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `Buffer.cs` — `[InlineArray]` on `record struct`\n\n**What breaks:** C# 13 now **prohibits** `[InlineArray]` on `record struct` types (it synthesizes `Equals`/`GetHashCode` that conflict with inline array layout).\n\n**Fix:** Change to a plain `struct`:\n\n```csharp\n[System.Runtime.CompilerServices.InlineArray(10)]\nstruct Buffer\n{\n    private int _element0;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `Generator.cs` — `stackalloc` in local function inside iterator\n\n**What breaks:** C# 13 relaxed `unsafe` restrictions in iterators/async methods, but as a side-effect the compiler now **hoists local functions** inside iterators into the state machine. `stackalloc` is still forbidden in state machines, so this now errors.\n\n**Fix:** Extract the local function to a regular `static` method on the class:\n\n```csharp\nunsafe class DataGenerator\n{\n    IEnumerable<int> Generate()\n    {\n        yield return 1;\n        Process();\n    }\n\n    static void Process()\n    {\n        int* p = stackalloc int[10];\n        // ... work with pointer\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `Resolver.cs` — Collection expression `[]` overload ambiguity\n\n**What breaks:** C# 13 added first-class implicit conversions for `Span<T>`/`ReadOnlySpan<T>`. The empty collection literal `[]` now matches **both** `ReadOnlySpan<int>` and `Span<object>`, causing an **ambiguity error** that didn't exist in C# 12.\n\n**Fix:** Disambiguate with an explicit type:\n\n```csharp\nstatic void Main()\n{\n    Process(ReadOnlySpan<int>.Empty);\n    // or: Process((ReadOnlySpan<int>)[]);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\nWant me to create these as actual files and verify they compile against .NET 9?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc1d48d8-03f4-407c-ba73-08a769de1749","outputTokens":505},"id":"f01b4fbd-6e92-4fae-b2ac-731f84fb2666","timestamp":"2026-04-08T01:14:45.351Z","parentId":"4a229052-a190-4c48-8457-662bb32b5685"}
